<H2><A NAME=SECTION00062000000000000000><A NAME=xref_forcing_a_relink>&#160;</A>Forcing a Re-Link</A></H2>
<P>
There are several ways to force a re-link of a <A HREF="node4.html#secthypertextdocuments">document</A> or
<A HREF="node9.html#sectdocumentlibraries">library</A>.
<P>
To re-link a particular document, or set of documents, from scratch,
their <A HREF="node18.html#sectindexfiles">index files</A> may simply be removed, using a command
such as:
<P>
<blockquote> <PRE>rm *.htx/htx.index
</PRE>
</blockquote>
<P>
The <A HREF="node48.html#hlink">linker</A> will then re-generate these indices and
consider the affected documents to have changed. They, and all other
documents that refer to them, will then be re-linked as
necessary. Alternatively, to re-link <b> all</b> documents from scratch
in this way, the <tt>-a</tt> flag may be given on the <tt>hlink</tt> command
line.
<P>
Removing the <A HREF="node19.html#sectlinkediting"><tt>&quot;</tt>htx.log<tt>&quot;</tt> date-stamp file</A>
from a document library will also force the documents in that library
to be re-linked but without unnecessarily re-generating any of its
index files.  This can be somewhat faster if the index files are known
to be up to date.
<P>
